node.text: Are you intimidated by wallpaper? I’m sharing the process in 30 seconds with a few of my favorite tips! node.text: Wallpaper is done!! 💃 One of those small unfinished projects checked off the list! Not sure if there’s a better to update a rom than a statement wallpaper.  This plaid wallpaper from @brewsterhome was love at first sight for me and helped me turn this space into the ultimate movie-watching room for our little family.  I reached out and they would love to help you guys create a dreamy room of your own!  One winner will receive a wallpaper feature wall of your choice!  Rules are simple… Like this post… comment and tag a wallpaper loving bestie… & follow @brewsterhome !! #sponsored #diywallpaper #wallpapergoals

node.text: Is this my house?  Does this convince anyone that painted brick is a good idea?  Anyone else as floored as I am?  Do you love this new take on the windows? So many questions!  I found @brickandbatten on Pinterest while searching for painted brick house inspiration and I’m so glad I did… They helped me visualize what I had in my head to transform this beautiful house and now I’m more motivated than ever to see this exterior renovation come to life.  Thoughts, questions, concerns… let’s hear them! #exteriorrenovation #paintedbrick

node.text: The drapes are hung and this arched window is looking oh so fine!  Grids or no grids?  I kinda love both if we are being honest.  I also thought about painting them black… So many options! I posted some other options I considered for arched window treatments on the blog in case you missed it.  And I’m really changing up how I show up everyday in case you missed that.  Such a fun week.  What do you guys think?  Oh, and you guys are the best most supportive community ever. #youguysrock #bestcommunity #archedwindowsforlife  Drapery: @uptowndrapes - Mora Plaid All other sources: posted on @all.things.mps

node.text: What a difference a few days make… and the perfect rug!  This space has been just waiting for a little TLC since we moved in and I’m pretty excited with how it’s coming together. #ad One of my best pro tips when designing a room is to start with a rug you love to really set the mood for the space. @rugs_usa has an incredible selection of rugs at great prices.. making it easy to find the one that will make your heart sing.  Head on over to stories to see this beauty up close and see more of my favorites!  #rugsusa

node.text: Did you see this color coming?  I did not! I originally was leaning towards something more moody, but this color pulled me in… it’s a beautiful warm gray beige with some hints of magenta and lavender depending on the light - it feels very sophisticated!  I’m picturing a beautiful upright piano in this little nook… what do you guys thing should go in here?  Next up… hardwood flooring going down tomorrow.  Filming some installation videos for you guys and will be sharing in stories… stay tuned! #beigeisback #makingprettyspaces #renolife  Color: @farrowandball Elephants Breath

node.text: Want the secret to controlling the dust when you renovate? Get a really good vacuum! #ad I feel like a total grown up with this new Oreck Command bagged vacuum… who knew they were so awesome!  Sharing everything I love about this new vacuum over in stories with a fun video.  Definitely a next level tool for your cleaning arsenal.  Who else loves their bagged vacuum? @oreckliving

node.text: Welcome to my new backyard!  I can’t tell you how happy this new view makes me. This past year has been full of ups and downs but one thing I’ve missed is entertaining and getting together with friends and family.  I partnered with @loweshomeimprovement to whip this outdoor space into shape for operation “neighborhood reunion”! Lowe’s has been a one stop resource for all things outdoor & entertaining.  I’m sharing some details of this amazing outdoor furniture in stories in case you’re planning a reunion of your own!  Share your own reunion plans and your best piece of outdoor entertaining advice – and you may just get a surprise to help with the finishing touches!  #LowesGoals #LowesPartner

node.text: The boys shared room!  I can’t believe how far it’s come with some cute accessories and paint (swipe to see it when we viewed the house). I get asked all the time about carpet in kids rooms and my answer is always an emphatic YES!  I chose this @stainmaster carpet for both design and function and couldn’t be happier with it. The extra thick carpet cushion makes it such a cozy spot for the kids to play - I’m always team carpet in kids spaces when it allows. In 3 short months, this carpet has already been tested to the max with spills and accidents and I can honestly say that STAINMASTER® lives up to its name 💯 percent!! #ad #stainmaster #lowesgoals #lowespartner

node.text: 2 easy outdoor DIY’s in 2 days! Who even am I?! I’m determined to get this back yard in shape by this weekend and I think I’m on track! Planter post for patio lights and a modern privacy fence… which one is your favorite? Both projects took less than 2 hours! I think I’ll add some flowers to this giant planter and have a glass of rose to celebrate some finished projects. Anyone going to build one of these this weekend? #outdoorrenovation #privacyfence #landscaping

node.text: Confused about a paint project? We’ve all been there! Getting advice from a pro is something we all want when tackling our projects and now you can! #sponsored @valsparpaint is launching their “Dial-a-Dad” hotline where you can text all your paint related questions and get dad-level advice from an expert! This is such a cool service just in time for Father’s Day to celebrate all those Dads out there providing the best advice and support. Even though Chris isn’t the painter in our household, he provides the heavy lifting and ALL the entertainment 😆. Who does the painting in your house? #ThanksValsparDads
